    "fact_id": "D2.21-rto-vs-rpo",
    "scope": "D2",
    "claim_type": "comparison",
    "status": "active",
    "claim": "RTO measures time to restore a function (how long the system can be down); RPO measures acceptable data loss in time (how old the recovered data can be). RTO is about system uptime; RPO is about data currency.",
